==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimension''' tool creates oblique chain dimensions: a sequence of aligned dimensions.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimensionExample.png|350px]]
{{Caption|On the right the created dimensions}}

==Usage==

# Select three or more vertexes.
# The two vertexes selected first define the direction and determine the position of the chain dimension.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* {{Version|1.0}}: If the {{MenuCommand|Dimensioning tools}} [[TechDraw_Preferences#Dimensions|preference]] is set to {{Value|Single tool}} (default): press the down arrow to the right of the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_Dimension.svg||x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimension.svg|16px]] Create Oblique Chain Dimensions}} option from the dropdown.
#* If this preference has a different value (and in {{VersionMinus|0.21}}): press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimension|Create Oblique Chain Dimensions]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Dimensions → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateObliqueChainDimension.svg|16px]] Create Oblique Chain Dimensions}} option from the menu.
# Chain dimensions with centered dimension texts are created.


